[{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"CurrentModule = GroupsOnGrids","category":"page"},{"location":"#GroupsOnGrids","page":"Home","title":"GroupsOnGrids","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"Documentation for GroupsOnGrids.","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"Modules = [GroupsOnGrids]","category":"page"},{"location":"#GroupsOnGrids.AxesInfo","page":"Home","title":"GroupsOnGrids.AxesInfo","text":"Represents the meaning of the axes of a signal.\n\nFields\n\nwidth: The axis of the signal representing the width.\nheight: The axis of the signal representing the height.\ndepth: The axis of the signal representing the depth.\ngroup: The axis of the signal representing the group element.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"#GroupsOnGrids.PointGroup","page":"Home","title":"GroupsOnGrids.PointGroup","text":"A point group is a group that leaves at least one element fixed. Here, they are the part of the space groups that do not involve translations. This leaves rotations and reflections.\n\nFields\n\nname::String: The name.\norder::Int: The number of elements.\ncomposition::Vector{Vector{Int}}: The composition table.\ninverses::Vector{Int}: The inverses.\nsubgroups::Dict{String,Vector{Int}}: The subgroups.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"#GroupsOnGrids.SpaceGroup","page":"Home","title":"GroupsOnGrids.SpaceGroup","text":"The space groups.\n\nEach space group is defined by a point group and a way of using it to act on a grid.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"#GroupsOnGrids.act_on_grid-Tuple{SpaceGroup, AbstractArray, AxesInfo, Int64}","page":"Home","title":"GroupsOnGrids.act_on_grid","text":"Apply a space group to a grid.\n\nArguments\n\ng: The group to apply.\nx: The grid to act on.\naxes: The meaning of the axes of the grid.\nnew_group_axis: The axis on which group actions should be concatenated.\n\nReturns\n\nThe grid after the group action has been applied.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#GroupsOnGrids.adjust_axes-Tuple{AxesInfo, Int64}","page":"Home","title":"GroupsOnGrids.adjust_axes","text":"In case the group axis comes before the width or height axis, we need to adjust the axes.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#GroupsOnGrids.lift-Tuple{AbstractArray, AxesInfo, Int64}","page":"Home","title":"GroupsOnGrids.lift","text":"Add a dimension to the signal representing the group element acted by.\n\nThe new group axis will bbe at the position new_group_axis, while the other axes maintain their relative order and are shifted accordingly.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#GroupsOnGrids.swap_axes-Tuple{AbstractArray, Any, Any}","page":"Home","title":"GroupsOnGrids.swap_axes","text":"Swap two given axes, keeping the other axes in their relative order.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"}]
